Turkey â€™s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  dropped 2 percent to 59,685.48 at the close in Istanbul,
the biggest decline in two months.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Seker Pilic & Yem Sanaii (SKPLC)   Ticaret AS (MGROS)  , a chicken
producer, added 3.9 percent to 2.13 liras after saying it would
set up a chain of restaurants on a franchise model.  Petkim Petrokimya Holding AS (PETKM)  , a chemicals maker,
fell 3.6 percent to 2.16 liras, its lowest in more than a month,
after 2011 profit missed estimates.  TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS (TAVHL)  , an airport
operator, sank 4.9 percent to 8.50 liras, its biggest loss in
almost seven months. A potential sale may be structured to avoid
a tender offer to minority shareholders, Chairman Hamdi Akin
told CNBC-e news channel today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
